					<category name="No Broken Chests Near Denial Subroutine">
						<comment># No Broken Chests Near Denial Subroutine v1.0.0</comment>
						<comment># by Apocalyptech</comment>
						<comment># Licensed under Public Domain / CC0 1.0 Universal</comment>
						<comment>#</comment>
						<comment># The Denial Subroutine arena (in Cluster 99002 0V3RL00K) has six bandit "coolers" which don't actually</comment>
						<comment># work -- they open and spawn their items, but the items can't actually be picked up.  This mod changes</comment>
						<comment># them to be the round ammo chests instead, so at least they work.</comment>
						<hotfix name="Name" level="Ma_RightCluster_P">
							<code profiles="default">set Ma_RightCluster_Combat.TheWorld:PersistentLevel.WillowPopulationOpportunityPoint_44 PopulationDef PopulationDefinition'GD_Ma_Population_Treasure.Lootables.BanditAmmo_Marigold'</code>
							<code profiles="default">set Ma_RightCluster_Combat.TheWorld:PersistentLevel.WillowPopulationOpportunityPoint_131 PopulationDef PopulationDefinition'GD_Ma_Population_Treasure.Lootables.BanditAmmo_Marigold'</code>
							<code profiles="default">set Ma_RightCluster_Combat.TheWorld:PersistentLevel.WillowPopulationOpportunityPoint_145 PopulationDef PopulationDefinition'GD_Ma_Population_Treasure.Lootables.BanditAmmo_Marigold'</code>
							<code profiles="default">set Ma_RightCluster_Combat.TheWorld:PersistentLevel.WillowPopulationOpportunityPoint_147 PopulationDef PopulationDefinition'GD_Ma_Population_Treasure.Lootables.BanditAmmo_Marigold'</code>
							<code profiles="default">set Ma_RightCluster_Combat.TheWorld:PersistentLevel.WillowPopulationOpportunityPoint_148 PopulationDef PopulationDefinition'GD_Ma_Population_Treasure.Lootables.BanditAmmo_Marigold'</code>
							<code profiles="default">set Ma_RightCluster_Combat.TheWorld:PersistentLevel.WillowPopulationOpportunityPoint_149 PopulationDef PopulationDefinition'GD_Ma_Population_Treasure.Lootables.BanditAmmo_Marigold'</code>
						</hotfix>
					</category>
					<category name="Guaranteed M0RQ, Cutie Killer, and Heartfull Splodger">
						<comment># Guaranteed M0RQ, Cutie Killer, and Heartfull Splodger v1.0.0</comment>
						<comment># by Apocalyptech</comment>
						<comment># Licensed under Public Domain / CC0 1.0 Universal</comment>
						<comment>#</comment>
						<comment># Ensures that the unique chests holding the M0RQ, Cutie Killer, and Heartfull Splodger</comment>
						<comment># will be openable -- avoids the glitch where sometimes a playthrough of Claptastic</comment>
						<comment># Voyage will have the chest already open, and the item therefore unobtainable.  This</comment>
						<comment># does lead to a side effect where these chests will be available again each time</comment>
						<comment># Borderlands is restarted.</comment>
						<category name="M0RQ, in Motherlessboard">
							<hotfix name="Name" level="Ma_Motherboard_P">
								<code profiles="default">set GD_Ma_Population_Treasure.InteractiveObjects.InteractiveObj_HiddenStash_03:BehaviorProviderDefinition_0 BehaviorSequences[0].EventData2[0].OutputLinks.ArrayIndexAndLength 262145</code>
							</hotfix>
						</category>
						<category name="Cutie Killer, in Subconscious">
							<hotfix name="Name" level="Ma_Subconscious_P">
								<code profiles="default">set GD_Ma_Population_Treasure.InteractiveObjects.InteractiveObj_HiddenStash_01:BehaviorProviderDefinition_0 BehaviorSequences[0].EventData2[0].OutputLinks.ArrayIndexAndLength 589825</code>
							</hotfix>
						</category>
						<category name="Heartfull Splodger, in Cluster 99002 0V3RL00K">
							<hotfix name="Name" level="Ma_RightCluster_P">
								<code profiles="default">set GD_Ma_Population_Treasure.InteractiveObjects.InteractiveObj_HiddenStash_02:BehaviorProviderDefinition_0 BehaviorSequences[0].EventData2[0].OutputLinks.ArrayIndexAndLength 393217</code>
							</hotfix>
						</category>
					</category>

				<category name="Skinpool Reassignments (DO NOT UNCHECK)" locked="true">
					<comment># TPS Skinpool Reassignments v1.1.0</comment>
					<comment># by Apocalyptech (based on the BL2 UCP section with the same purpose)</comment>
					<comment># Licensed under Public Domain / CC0 1.0 Universal</comment>
					<comment>#</comment>
					<comment># Frees up 624 skin/head pools for use by TPS mods.  This</comment>
					<comment># is possible because the default skin/head pools use an effectively</comment>
					<comment># unnecessary intermediate pool inbetween the pool that's actually</comment>
					<comment># used for drops and the skins/heads themselves.  The BL2 UCP does</comment>
					<comment># this and uses the resulting pools for custom boss drops, and</comment>
					<comment># other mods do so as well.</comment>
					<comment>#</comment>
					<comment># See https://github.com/BLCM/BLCMods/wiki/TPS-Custom-Skin-and-Head-Pool-Registry</comment>
					<category name="Skinpool Hotfixes">
						<hotfix name="ApocHotfix" level="None">

				<category name="Spawn Only COMs of your character">
					<comment># TPS No Wasted COMs v1.1.0</comment>
					<comment># by Apocalyptech</comment>
					<comment># Licensed under Public Domain / CC0 1.0 Universal</comment>
					<comment>#</comment>
					<comment># Sets the game to only drop COMs for the player classes who are actually</comment>
					<comment># in the game at the time.  Once a player class has joined the game, the</comment>
					<comment># only way to remove that character's COMs from the drop pools is to exit</comment>
					<comment># to the main menu and re-execute the patch.</comment>
					<category name="Initial Clear">
						<comment># Do an initial set to clear out the COM item pools.  This is actually</comment>
						<comment># only required if you're looking to "clear out" a pool after a character's</comment>
						<comment># left the game, and must be done by exiting out to the main menu and re-</comment>
						<comment># executing the mod/patch.</comment>

			<category name="mods">
			</category>
			<category name="Economy Fixes & Improvements TPS (imported from root)">
				<comment># Economy Fixes & Improvements (By Seud)</comment>
				<comment># The Pre-Sequel Edition</comment>
				<comment> </comment>
				<comment># In Borderlands 2 and TPS, vending machines and money serve a very limited purpose.</comment>
				<comment># Regular items shown for sale are only useful for leveling if no good loot has been found, as they cannot be better than green</comment>
				<comment># IotD distribution, while improved from Borderlands 2, could still be better</comment>
				<comment># Only slot machines are slightly useful, but their chances for purple and legendaries are low too - they are mostly good for Moonstones</comment>
				<comment># In addition to that, there are lots of anomalies and inconsistencies in how item prices are calculated, which makes modding values harder</comment>
				<comment># This mod attempts to fix all of this by using money and machines as a supplementary source of loot rather than functional decoration</comment>
				<comment># Each feature has a description of its changes</comment>
				<comment># The mod is modular so if you don't like one feature, you can choose to not enable it. All presets also have "Vanilla" options.</comment>
				<category name="Price Calculation Fixes (Heavily recommended, Required for BRP)">
					<comment># Fixes a lot of weird quirks and arbitrary decisions in how some prices are calculated</comment>
					<comment># Affects all launchers, many weapon parts, Legendary Grenade Mods and some Legendary Shields</comment>
					<comment># Required for "Better Rarity Prices" to work properly, but does not require it</comment>
					<comment># Heavily recommended either way</comment>
					<category name="Fix Grenade mods">
						<comment># By default, Grenade mods use their Damage and StatusDamage for their price modifications.</comment>
						<comment># This means that Legendaries and Very Rare mods are worth the same.</comment>
						<comment># Here, we change it so the Material holds the rarity mod instead, allowing proper scaling.</comment>
						<category name="Add APR to Materials">

					</category>
					<category name="Fix Weapons">
						<comment># In Vanilla, weapons use two types of MonetaryValueMod modifiers</comment>
						<comment># APR (Att_Price_Rarity) is common to all items and apply a major modifier to price based on item rarity</comment>
						<comment># WCM (WeaponCostModifier) is only present on weapon parts and apply a minor adjustment based on better/extra parts (e.g. accessories)</comment>
						<comment># In theory, APR is used once and only once for every piece of equipment based on its rarity and WCM is used multiple times</comment>
						<comment># In practice however, there are many inconsistencies in which either are used, leading to bizarre values for some weapons</comment>
						<comment># This also means that changing the APR will affect some weapons multiple times and others not at all</comment>
						<comment># Here, we focus APRs on Materials instead of Bodies/Barrels to make the calculation consistent with Relics/Shields and easily moddable</comment>
						<comment># We also fix a few other minor inconsistencies</comment>
						<category name="Transfer APR from Body/Barrel to Material">
							<comment># By default, Common to Very Rare APR mults are managed on the weapon Body, and legendaries have their Barrel increase in price instead</comment>
							<comment># This is not only inconsistent with the behavior of other items, it also means that legendaries apply APRs twice : From both body (incorrectly) and barrel</comment>
							<comment># The consistent way of doing things is to manage APR on materials instead, which are always matched to rarity, the same way Shields work</comment>
							<category name="Remove APR from Bodies & Barrels">
								<code profiles="default">set gd_cork_weap_assaultrifle.Barrel.AR_Barrel_Dahl_HammerBreaker MonetaryValueMod None</code>
								<code profiles="default">set gd_cork_weap_assaultrifle.Barrel.AR_Barrel_Dahl_MajorTom MonetaryValueMod None</code>
								<code profiles="default">set gd_cork_weap_assaultrifle.Barrel.AR_Barrel_Torgue_KerBoom MonetaryValueMod None</code>
								<code profiles="default">set gd_cork_weap_assaultrifle.Barrel.AR_Barrel_Vladof_IceScream MonetaryValueMod None</code>
								<code profiles="default">set gd_cork_weap_assaultrifle.Barrel.AR_Barrel_Vladof_OldPainful MonetaryValueMod None</code>

								<code profiles="default">set GD_Cork_Weap_Lasers.Body.Laser_Body_Dahl_3 MonetaryValueMod None</code>

						<comment># UCP fixes their rarity, this fixes their value</comment>

				<category name="Better Rarity Prices" MUT="true">
					<comment># Makes rarity of items affect their value more (Lowers value of Common and Uncommon items, raises value of Very Rare and up items)</comment>
					<comment># In the base game, a legendary can be worth less than 6 whites. Now, a Legendary item has a price worthy of its power !</comment>
					<comment># If you pick a non-Vanilla distribution, I recommend making the money level scaling softer (Using SPC) or many items will reach the cap at high levels</comment>
					<category name="Balanced">
						<comment># Price progression is more distinct than Vanilla</comment>
						<comment># Difference between rarities rise with them</comment>
						<comment># Use this if you want my recommended experience</comment>
						<code profiles="default">set GD_Economy.Rarity.Att_Price_RarityMultiplier_01_Common:ConstantAttributeValueResolver_0 ConstantValue 0.5</code>
						<code profiles="default">set GD_Economy.Rarity.Att_Price_RarityMultiplier_02_Uncommon:ConstantAttributeValueResolver_0 ConstantValue 1</code>
						<code profiles="default">set GD_Economy.Rarity.Att_Price_RarityMultiplier_03_Rare:ConstantAttributeValueResolver_0 ConstantValue 2.5</code>
						<code profiles="default">set GD_Economy.Rarity.Att_Price_RarityMultiplier_04_VeryRare:ConstantAttributeValueResolver_0 ConstantValue 8</code>
						<code profiles="default">set GD_Economy.Rarity.Att_Price_RarityMultiplier_05_Legendary:ConstantAttributeValueResolver_0 ConstantValue 30</code>
					</category>
					<category name="x10">
						<comment># Price progression strictly follows the game default rarity ditribution</comment>
						<comment># Every rarity costs x10 compared to the previous rarity</comment>
						<comment># Use this if you like high numbers on rarer stuff</comment>
						<code profiles="">set GD_Economy.Rarity.Att_Price_RarityMultiplier_01_Common:ConstantAttributeValueResolver_0 ConstantValue 0.1</code>
						<code profiles="">set GD_Economy.Rarity.Att_Price_RarityMultiplier_02_Uncommon:ConstantAttributeValueResolver_0 ConstantValue 1</code>
						<code profiles="">set GD_Economy.Rarity.Att_Price_RarityMultiplier_03_Rare:ConstantAttributeValueResolver_0 ConstantValue 10</code>
						<code profiles="">set GD_Economy.Rarity.Att_Price_RarityMultiplier_04_VeryRare:ConstantAttributeValueResolver_0 ConstantValue 100</code>
						<code profiles="">set GD_Economy.Rarity.Att_Price_RarityMultiplier_05_Legendary:ConstantAttributeValueResolver_0 ConstantValue 1000</code>
					</category>
					<category name="Vanilla">
						<comment># Price progression is strictly vanilla</comment>
						<comment># Cost does not increase a lot between rarities</comment>
						<comment># Use this if you only want the price consistency improvements</comment>
						<code profiles="">set GD_Economy.Rarity.Att_Price_RarityMultiplier_01_Common:ConstantAttributeValueResolver_0 ConstantValue 0.96</code>
						<code profiles="">set GD_Economy.Rarity.Att_Price_RarityMultiplier_02_Uncommon:ConstantAttributeValueResolver_0 ConstantValue 1.6</code>
						<code profiles="">set GD_Economy.Rarity.Att_Price_RarityMultiplier_03_Rare:ConstantAttributeValueResolver_0 ConstantValue 2.6</code>
						<code profiles="">set GD_Economy.Rarity.Att_Price_RarityMultiplier_04_VeryRare:ConstantAttributeValueResolver_0 ConstantValue 3.6</code>
						<code profiles="">set GD_Economy.Rarity.Att_Price_RarityMultiplier_05_Legendary:ConstantAttributeValueResolver_0 ConstantValue 5.6</code>
					</category>
				</category>
				<category name="Softer Price Curve" MUT="true">
					<comment># Lowers the effect of level on money sources and prices</comment>
					<category name="Soft (Good for Balanced)">
						<code profiles="default">set GD_Economy.Universal.Att_UniversalPriceIncreasePerLevelScaler:ConstantAttributeValueResolver_1 ConstantValue 1.08</code>
					</category>
					<category name="Softer (Good for x10)">
						<code profiles="">set GD_Economy.Universal.Att_UniversalPriceIncreasePerLevelScaler:ConstantAttributeValueResolver_1 ConstantValue 1.06</code>
					</category>
					<category name="Negligible">
						<code profiles="">set GD_Economy.Universal.Att_UniversalPriceIncreasePerLevelScaler:ConstantAttributeValueResolver_1 ConstantValue 1.01</code>
					</category>
					<category name="Vanilla">
						<code profiles="">set GD_Economy.Universal.Att_UniversalPriceIncreasePerLevelScaler:ConstantAttributeValueResolver_1 ConstantValue 1.12</code>
					</category>
				</category>
				<category name="More Rewarding Quests" MUT="true">
					<comment># Quest money rewards are pretty lackluster in the base game</comment>
					<comment># This increases them, making completing quests grant a boost that is noticeable compared to selling loot and picking up raw cash</comment>
					<category name="Balanced">
						<code profiles="default">set GD_Economy.Missions.Att_BaseCredits_MissionRewards:ConstantAttributeValueResolver_0 ConstantValue 200</code>
					</category>
					<category name="Vanilla">
						<code profiles="">set GD_Economy.Missions.Att_BaseCredits_MissionRewards:ConstantAttributeValueResolver_0 ConstantValue 40.5</code>
					</category>
				</category>
				<category name="Change Markup" MUT="true">
					<comment># Changes how much Vendors charge for items compared to their base value</comment>
					<comment># Vanilla is actually best but you can also use Borderlands 1 markup instead, which is fixed, or BOrderlands 2 which is lower</comment>
					<category name="Balanced (Vanilla)">
						<hotfix name="EFI" level="None">
							<code profiles="">set GD_Economy.VendingMachine.Att_BaseVendingMarkupIncrease:ConstantAttributeValueResolver_0 ConstantValue 6.2</code>
							<code profiles="">set GD_Economy.VendingMachine.Att_SellExponentializer:ConstantAttributeValueResolver_0 ConstantValue 0.15</code>
						</hotfix>
					</category>
					<category name="Borderlands 2">
						<hotfix name="Custom" level="None">
							<code profiles="default">set GD_Economy.VendingMachine.Att_BaseVendingMarkupIncrease:ConstantAttributeValueResolver_0 ConstantValue 4.1</code>
							<code profiles="default">set GD_Economy.VendingMachine.Att_SellExponentializer:ConstantAttributeValueResolver_0 ConstantValue 0.14</code>
						</hotfix>
						<category name="Vanilla's inversion">
							<category name="Sucesfully inverted">

			<category name="TPS Early Bloomer (imported from root)">
				<comment># TPS Early Bloomer v1.1.0</comment>
				<comment># by Apocalyptech</comment>
				<comment># Licensed under Public Domain / CC0 1.0 Universal</comment>
				<comment>#</comment>
				<comment># This mod is an improvement on the similar section from UCP 2.1 which unlocks various</comment>
				<comment># equipment in the game.  In addition to the basic early-game weapon unlocks that UCP</comment>
				<comment># provides, this additionally allows Relics, Class Mods, all shield types, all grenade</comment>
				<comment># types, and probably just about everything to spawn from the beginning.</comment>
				<comment>#</comment>
				<comment># There's no problem with having both this and UCP enabled -- it'll just mean</comment>
				<comment># that a few statements get executed twice.</comment>
				<category name="Main Unlocks">
					<comment># Note that we omit Gamestage_24 on purpose here, because that is used to</comment>

			<category name="TPS Configurable Slot Machines (imported from root)">
				<comment># TPS Configurable Slot Machines v1.0.0</comment>
				<comment># by Apocalyptech</comment>
				<comment># Licensed under Public Domain / CC0 1.0 Universal</comment>
				<comment>#</comment>
				<comment># Allows you to configure the base game's slot machines, of the sort in Concordia.</comment>
				<comment># The default configuration is identical to the stock slot machines - you must choose</comment>
				<comment># some options to actually have any changes take effect.</comment>
				<comment>#</comment>
				<comment># Keep in mind that increasing the frequency of one kind of item can end up impacting</comment>
				<comment># the frequencies of other items.  Categories with "Quality" in the title should keep</comment>
				<comment># the frequencies the same.</comment>
				<comment>#</comment>
				<comment># Also note that if you're in developer mode in BLCMM v1.1.6, most of this mod will</comment>
				<comment># complain that things will be overwritten by the game -- that's actually an error on</comment>
				<comment># BLCMM's part, and should hopefully be fixed by v1.1.7.</comment>
				<category name="Mod Setup" locked="true">
					<comment># These are some statements which are required for some of the later statements</comment>
					<comment># to work properly.</comment>
					<hotfix name="ApocHotfix" level="None">
						<code profiles="default">set GD_SlotMachine.SlotMachine:BehaviorProviderDefinition_0 BehaviorSequences[1].BehaviorData2[4].LinkedVariables.ArrayIndexAndLength 0</code>

			<category name="TPS - Respawning Loot (imported from root)">
				<comment>Mod written by GitHub: (Our Lord And Savior Gabe Newell) / Nexus Mods: (OB4MA)</comment>
				<comment></comment>
				<comment>This mod makes all objects refresh themselves upon leaving and re-entering the map.</comment>
				<comment>This allows you to keep getting stuff without save and quitting.</comment>
				<comment>This refreshes vendors too.  So now the timer for the item of the day is only if you stay in that map for however long.</comment>
				<comment>As far as I am aware it does NOT affect enemies at all.</comment>
				<comment></comment>
				<category name="Super Complicated Stuff - Leave Enabled" locked="true">
					<category name="Code">
						<code profiles="default">set GearboxFramework.Default__PopulationDefinition bTotalResetOnLevelLoad True</code>
					</category>
				</category>
			</category>
			<category name="Omni-Cannon with Grenade Damage v1.0.0 (imported from root)">
				<comment>Mod author: Astor</comment>
				<comment>Release Date: 15 November 2018</comment>
				<comment>Version: 1.0.0 - See ReadMe for Changelog ;)</comment>
				<category name="Description">
					<comment>While TPS UCP 2.2 upgrades to the Omni-Cannon have made it a MUCH more valuable piece,</comment>
					<comment>it still does not become viable enough for most characters; but with this Grenade Damage Bonus added,  </comment>
					<comment>the Omni-Cannon will become one of the BEST snipers in TPS. </comment>
				</category>
				<category name="Grenade Damage Bonus">
					<code profiles="default">set GD_Ma_Weapons.FiringModes.Bullet_Sniper_OmniCannon:Behavior_Explode_34 DamageSource Class'WillowGame.WillowDmgSource_Grenade'</code>
				</category>
			</category>
			<category name="Respawning Enemies And Allies (imported from root)">
				<comment>Mod written by GitHub: (Our Lord And Savior Gabe Newell) / Nexus Mods: (OB4MA)</comment>
				<comment></comment>
				<comment>This mod makes all enemy and ally spawns refresh upon map exit and re-entering.</comment>
				<comment>This allows you to keep getting stuff without save and quitting.</comment>
				<comment>For example, you can farm the Bunker, Doc Mercy, Boll and whoever else who doesn't normally respawn without save and quitting.</comment>
				<comment>This can be useful for things like Anarchy stacks.</comment>
				<comment></comment>
				<category name="Super Complicated Stuff - Leave Enabled" locked="true">
					<category name="Code">
						<code profiles="default">set WillowGame.Default__WillowPopulationDefinition bTotalResetOnLevelLoad True</code>
					</category>
				</category>
				<comment></comment>
				<comment>OPTIONAL: Customize this part to your liking, the default value here is the normal respawn delay.</comment>
				<comment></comment>
				<category name="OPTIONAL: Change Respawn Delay For AI.">
					<code profiles="">set GD_Globals.General.Globals RespawnDelayInSeconds 1500.000000</code>
				</category>
			</category>
			<category name="Fast Travel Helper (imported from root)">
				<comment>By apple1417</comment>
				<comment>Allows you re-enable the previously one-way only fast travel stations, lets you move them to any</comment>
				<comment> map without one, and adds a few QoL changes to go along with these new stations</comment>
				<comment>Note that moving these stations away from their default location may cause issues when playing</comment>
				<comment> through the story</comment>
				<category name="Fast Travel Stations">
					<category name="Titan Robot Embarkation" MUT="true">
						<category name="Default">
							<code profiles="">set GD_FastTravelStations.DahlFactoryBoss bSendOnly False</code>
							<code profiles="">set GD_FastTravelStations.DahlFactoryBoss AccessibilityTime FTAT_Always</code>
						</category>
						<category name="Helios Station">
							<code profiles="">set GD_FastTravelStations.DahlFactoryBoss bSendOnly False</code>

					<category name="Move 00773 Vault Excavation Site next to Cluster 00773 in station list">
						<code profiles="default">set FastTravelStationsListOrder'GD_Ma_FastTravelStations.Ma_StationsList' FastTravelStationOrderList (FastTravelStationDefinition'GD_FastTravelStations.Spaceport',FastTravelStationDefinition'GD_Ma_FastTravelStations.Ma_Deck13_FT',FastTravelStationDefinition'GD_Ma_FastTravelStations.Ma_Nexus_FT',FastTravelStationDefinition'GD_Ma_FastTravelStations.Ma_LeftCluster_FT',FastTravelStationDefinition'GD_Ma_FastTravelStations.Ma_LeftCluster_1way_FT',FastTravelStationDefinition'GD_Ma_FastTravelStations.Ma_RightCluster_FT',FastTravelStationDefinition'GD_Ma_FastTravelStations.Ma_Sub_FT',FastTravelStationDefinition'GD_Ma_FastTravelStations.MA_SubSub_FT',FastTravelStationDefinition'GD_Ma_FastTravelStations.Ma_FinalBoss_FT')</code>
					</category>
					<category name="Re-enable Eye of Helios level transition">
						<hotfix name="EnableLaserBossTravel" level="Laser_P">
							<code profiles="">set SeqAct_ToggleHidden'Laser_P.TheWorld:PersistentLevel.Main_Sequence.SeqAct_ToggleHidden_1' OutputLinks ()</code>
							<code profiles="">set SeqAct_ToggleHidden'Laser_P.TheWorld:PersistentLevel.Main_Sequence.SeqAct_ToggleHidden_1' VariableLinks ()</code>
							<code profiles="">set SeqAct_Toggle'Laser_P.TheWorld:PersistentLevel.Main_Sequence.SeqAct_Toggle_4' OutputLinks ()</code>
							<code profiles="">set SeqAct_Toggle'Laser_P.TheWorld:PersistentLevel.Main_Sequence.SeqAct_Toggle_4' VariableLinks ()</code>
						</hotfix>
					</category>
					<category name="Respawnable Flameknuckle">
						<hotfix name="RespawnFlame" level="MoonShotIntro_P">
							<code profiles="default">set PopulationOpportunityDen'MoonShotIntro_Dynamic.TheWorld:PersistentLevel.PopulationOpportunityDen_0' IsEnabled True</code>
							<code profiles="default">set PopulationOpportunityDen'MoonShotIntro_Dynamic.TheWorld:PersistentLevel.PopulationOpportunityDen_0' bUseRandomSpawns False</code>
						</hotfix>
					</category>
					<category name="Respawnable Zarpedon">
						<comment>Note that having "Skip Powersuit Phase" selected will spawn both forms during the story,</comment>
						<comment> and that killing Ascended Zarpedon before the objective to do so will cause a softlock</comment>
						<category name="Options" MUT="true">
							<category name="Standard">
								<hotfix name="RespawnZarpMech" level="LaserBoss_P">
									<code profiles="default">set PopulationOpportunityDen'LaserBoss_Boss.TheWorld:PersistentLevel.PopulationOpportunityDen_3' IsEnabled True</code>
									<code profiles="default">set PopulationOpportunityDen'LaserBoss_Boss.TheWorld:PersistentLevel.PopulationOpportunityDen_3' bUseRandomSpawns False</code>
								</hotfix>
							</category>
							<category name="Skip Powersuit Phase">

			<category name="No More Reload Messages v1.0.0 (imported from root)">
				<comment>Mod author: Astor</comment>
				<comment>Release Date: 06 November 2018</comment>

				<comment>Removes the "Reload Message" which pop-up (too) often on the screen!</comment>

			<category name="TPS - Uncapped Pause / Main Menu Settings (imported from root)">
				<comment>Mod written by GitHub: Our Lord And Savior Gabe Newell / Nexus Mods: OB4MA</comment>
				<comment></comment>
				<comment>This mod simply allows more customization in terms of scrollable settings accessed via the pause or main menu.</comment>
				<comment>These settings, unlike other methods, WILL KEEP THE VALUE even if you do not execute the mod again.</comment>
				<comment>However, if you mess with them again they will go back to normal value ranges.</comment>
				<comment></comment>
				<comment>There is nothing to customize in this file, you do all of the customizing in-game.</comment>
				<comment>You can edit the ranges for values if you would like to.</comment>
				<comment></comment>
				<comment>-----------------------------------------</comment>
				<category name="Player FOV">
					<category name="Code">
						<hotfix name="Options" level="None">
							<code profiles="default">set Transient.WillowProfileSettings_0 ProfileMappings[23] (Id=129,Name="PlayerFOV",ColumnHeaderText=,MappingType=PVMT_RawValue,ValueMappings=,PredefinedValues=,MinVal=1,MaxVal=179,RangeIncrement=1)</code>
						</hotfix>
					</category>
				</category>

					<category name="Deadly Bloom">
